==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: malaria
<hw>ma*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It., contr. fr.
<ets>malaaria</ets> bad air. See <er>Malice</er>, and Air.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Air infected with some noxious substance capable of
engendering disease; esp., an unhealthy exhalation from certain soils,
as marshy or wet lands, producing fevers; miasma.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The morbific agent in malaria is supposed by some to be
a vegetable microbe or its spores, and by others to be a very minute
animal blood parasite (an <xex>infusorian</xex>).</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A human disease caused by
infection of red blood cells by a protozoan of the genus
<gen>Plasmodium</gen>, giving rise to fever and chills and many other
symptoms, characterized by their tendency to recur at definite and
usually uniform intervals. The protozoal infection is usually
transmitted from another infected individual by the bite of an
<gen>Anopheles</gen> mosquito.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malarious</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Malarian</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Malarial</ent>⟦br⟧
